HEADWORD: Enecate
<hw>En"e*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>enecatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>enecare</ets>; <ets>e</ets> out,
utterly + <ets>necare</ets> to kill.]</ety> <def>To kill off; to
destroy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Harvey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

